    <section class="section challenge-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">The Challenge</h2>
            <p class="section-content">
                Huddle House, a growing restaurant chain, was struggling with manual billing processes that were consuming significant time and creating costly errors. Their existing system required extensive manual data entry and reconciliation across multiple vendors and payment systems.
            </p>
            <div class="challenge-grid">
                <div class="challenge-item">
                    <h4>Manual Invoice Processing</h4>
                    <p>Staff spent hours manually entering vendor invoices, cross-referencing orders, and reconciling discrepancies. This process was error-prone and time-consuming.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="challenge-item">
                    <h4>Vendor Payment Delays</h4>
                    <p>Complex approval workflows and manual payment processing led to delayed vendor payments, straining relationships and occasionally missing early payment discounts.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="challenge-item">
                    <h4>Cash Flow Visibility</h4>
                    <p>Lack of real-time financial data made it difficult to manage cash flow effectively and make informed business decisions about inventory and operations.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

